!! What It Does

The ''Simple Outline'' plugin adds a `<$simple-outline>` widget that renders a collapsible, nested outline from a plain-text description.  Each node can reference a tiddler — when the tiddler has body text, the node becomes expandable and shows that content inline.  Open/closed state is preserved for the duration of the session.

!! Installation

Drag [[$:/plugins/crosseye/simple-outline]] tiddler to any TW5 wiki (version 5.3.0 or later) and save.

!! Usage

```
<$simple-outline text="""
!! Section heading

  Group label
    + tiddler-name
    + display text :: tiddler-title

  Another group
    + another-tiddler
""" class="outline"/>
```

The `text` attribute holds the outline description.  You can also supply it via transclusion: `text={{MyOutlineTiddler}}`.

!!! Input format

|!Syntax |!Meaning |
|`!! Heading` |Section header (renders as `<h2>`) |
|`+ tiddler-name` |Tiddler reference — expandable if the tiddler has body text |
|`label :: tiddler-name` |Override the display label for a tiddler reference |
|Plain text |Structural group — collapsible if it has children |
|Indentation |Nesting — each extra level of leading spaces is one level deeper |

!!! Label resolution

For tiddler references, the displayed label is taken from the first non-empty value in the `label-fields` chain (default: `summary` → `caption`), falling back to the name as written.

!!! Attributes

|!Attribute |!Default |!Purpose |
|`text` |— |The outline description (required) |
|`class` |`outline` |CSS class(es) on the container `<div>` |
|`summary-template` |— |Tiddler to render inside each `<summary>` for tiddler items; receives `currentTiddler` and `so-label` |
|`group-template` |— |Tiddler to render inside each `<summary>` for group nodes; receives `so-label` only |
|`header-template` |— |Tiddler to render inside `!!` section headers, replacing the default `<h2>`; receives `so-label` only |
|`detail-template` |— |Tiddler to render as the expanded body for each tiddler item; receives `currentTiddler` and `so-label` |
|`tiddler-link` |— |When non-empty, adds a link on each tiddler item's row that opens the tiddler without toggling the node |
|`open-depth` |`0` |Levels to open by default on first render |
|`label-fields` |`summary caption` |Space-separated field names tried in order for the display label |

!! The Demos

!!! [[History of Computing Outline Demo]]

A personal knowledge management example showing 4–5 levels of nesting.  Each `+ note-*` entry references a real tiddler with a `summary` field (used as the label) and body text (shown when expanded).  This is the most straightforward use of the plugin: write your outline, create your note tiddlers, and the structure takes care of itself.

!!! [[Acts 7 Outline Demo]]

Shows the `summary-template` attribute in action.  The template renders a custom label-plus-toggle structure, and the `outline-acts` CSS class replaces the default arrow icon with a red `+`/`–` toggle positioned directly after each label.  This demo illustrates how the default styling can be overridden entirely through CSS and a small template tiddler — no changes to the plugin are needed.

!!! [[Detail Template Test Demo]]

Shows the `detail-template` attribute in action.  Instead of transcluding a tiddler's body text directly, the plugin renders the named template tiddler with `currentTiddler` and `so-label` set.  The template here adds a linked title above the body so the reader can navigate to the source tiddler directly.

!!! [[Tiddler Link Demo]]

Shows the `tiddler-link` attribute: each tiddler item gets a small ✳ link on the right of its summary row.  Clicking it opens the tiddler in the story river without toggling the outline node, so you can read entries without losing your place.  Also uses `open-depth="1"` (added in 0.7.0) to pre-open the top level on first visit.

!!! [[Styled Outline Demo]]

Shows `group-template` and `header-template` together, giving the structural nodes a custom visual style.  The header template replaces the default `<h2>` with a ruled heading.  The group template renders labels in bold italic — and, because templates have full TW widget access, conditionally appends a short description from the group's own tiddler when one exists.

!!! [[WikiText Reference Outline Demo]]

Demonstrates that the outline structure stands on its own even when the referenced tiddlers don't exist locally.  The entry names are real tiddler titles from the main site -- drag <span style="color: #5778d8; text-decoration: underline; cursor: grab;"><$draggable filter="[[$:/plugins/crosseye/simple-outline]] [[WikiText Reference Outline Demo]]" tag="span">the plugin and the outline tiddler</$draggable></span> to [[tiddlywiki.com|https://tiddlywiki.com]], save and refresh to see it populated with live content. (A link to this tiddler will show up at the top of the table of contents.).  //Note that no tiddlers were harmed in the creation of this outline.//
